    <h1>BadCourt API Documentation</h1>
    <p>
      Welcome to the BadCourt API. This API allows you to interact, retrieve and
      access data from the BadCourt database. Please refer to the documentation
      below for details on how to interact with the API.
    </p>
    <li>
      This API is connect directly to the BadCourt database. All users must be
      super carefully to use this (recommend: just use for testing the api
      endpoints).
    </li>
    <li>
      This API is just for internal requirements and should not be published
      outside.
    </li>
    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Most of the APIs required <strong>Bearer Token Authentication</strong>.
        Use your username and password to get a token obtained from the
        <code>/api/login</code> endpoint.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <br />

    <!-- POST /login -->
    <div class="endpoint">
      <h2 class="get-method">POST /login</h2>
      <p>
        Returns the user with specific email and password, assign with token
        generated by the server. No authentication is required.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Request Body:</strong></p>
      <pre><code>{
  "email": "The email of the user.",
  "password": "The password of the user."
}</code></pre>
      <div class="example">
        <p><strong>Example Request:</strong></p>
        <div class="request">
          <code
            ><span class="post-method">POST</span> http://localhost:<%= port
            %>/api/login</code
          >
          <pre><code>{
  "email": "example@gmail.com",
  "password": "examplePassword"
}</code></pre>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request successfully:</li>
          <div class="response">
            <pre><code>{
  "token": "generated-token",
  "_id": "user-id",
  "name": "user-name",
  "email": "example@gmail.com",
  "password": "hashed-and-salted-password",
  "address": "user-address",
  "role": "user",
  "__v": 1
}
</code></pre>
          </div>
          <li>If the email does not exist:</li>
          <div class="response">
            <pre><code>{
  "msg": "User with this email does not exist!"
}
</code></pre>
          </div>
          <li>Incorrect password:</li>
          <div class="response">
            <pre><code>{
  "msg": "Incorrect password!"
}
</code></pre>
          </div>
          <li>Internal server error:</li>
          <div class="response">
            <pre><code>{
  "error": "error-message"
}
</code></pre>
          </div>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
